1
00:00:07,958 --> 00:00:08,916
♪

2
00:00:09,000 --> 00:00:10,291
[indistinct chatter]

3
00:00:46,583 --> 00:00:48,291
Okay then,
the last item on my list

4
00:00:48,375 --> 00:00:50,500
is the cat ears
that Katsuragi wanted.

5
00:00:50,583 --> 00:00:52,500
But I don't have any idea
what kind of store

6
00:00:52,583 --> 00:00:53,708
would sell
something like that.

7
00:00:53,791 --> 00:00:56,041
Hey, Asuka!

8
00:00:56,125 --> 00:00:57,583
Yumi?

9
00:01:00,291 --> 00:01:01,625
That's a lot of bags!

10
00:01:01,708 --> 00:01:03,291
Are you doing your
Christmas shopping?

11
00:01:03,375 --> 00:01:05,208
Yeah, it looks like we both are!

12
00:01:05,291 --> 00:01:07,083
You have quite a few
bags yourself.

13
00:01:09,291 --> 00:01:11,375
You caught me!

14
00:01:11,458 --> 00:01:14,833
'Tis the season.
That reminds me,

15
00:01:14,916 --> 00:01:17,750
I'm actually looking for a pair
of kitty ears for a friend.

16
00:01:17,833 --> 00:01:19,875
Know where I might be able
to find some?

17
00:01:19,958 --> 00:01:21,083
Kitty ears, huh?

18
00:01:21,166 --> 00:01:22,250
Yeah.

19
00:01:22,333 --> 00:01:23,958
For whatever reason,
Katsuragi really

20
00:01:24,041 --> 00:01:25,958
wants them
for Christmas this year.

21
00:01:26,041 --> 00:01:27,208
Which is kind of weird,

22
00:01:27,291 --> 00:01:29,500
because cat ears
aren't usually her style.

23
00:01:29,583 --> 00:01:31,750
Knowing her, she'll probably
just make me or Ikaruga

24
00:01:31,833 --> 00:01:33,916
wear them to fulfill
her gross fantasies.

25
00:01:38,958 --> 00:01:42,083
There's a store close to here
that would probably have them.

26
00:01:42,166 --> 00:01:44,041
Why don't we go check it
out together.

27
00:01:44,125 --> 00:01:45,041
For real?

28
00:01:45,125 --> 00:01:46,208
Yeah, but we'll have
to hurry

29
00:01:46,291 --> 00:01:48,041
because they close
kind of early.

30
00:01:49,625 --> 00:01:51,416
Come on, Asuka!

31
00:02:08,958 --> 00:02:10,041
[YUMI]
It's snowing!

32
00:02:10,125 --> 00:02:11,875
[ASUKA]
How pretty!

33
00:02:14,875 --> 00:02:16,250
I hope it keeps up.

34
00:02:16,333 --> 00:02:18,125
Maybe we'll have
a white Christmas.

35
00:02:19,250 --> 00:02:20,208
Yeah.

36
00:02:20,291 --> 00:02:21,208
Maybe.

37
00:02:24,041 --> 00:02:26,291
[YUMI]
Snow is beautiful.

38
00:02:26,375 --> 00:02:28,708
But even the whitest snow
will mix with the dirt

39
00:02:28,791 --> 00:02:31,000
and disappear
when it touches the ground.

40
00:02:36,333 --> 00:02:40,750
The truth is, the world isn't
just full of pretty things.

41
00:02:40,833 --> 00:02:44,250
[ASUKA] Where there is light,
there is also darkness.

42
00:02:44,333 --> 00:02:47,333
This is the story
of a select group of girls.

43
00:02:47,416 --> 00:02:50,166
They are the shinobi warriors
who live in the shadows.

44
00:02:55,291 --> 00:02:56,333
[YUMI]
Yah!

45
00:02:59,458 --> 00:03:00,500
[ASUKA shouts]

46
00:03:27,666 --> 00:03:28,708
[cat meows]

47
00:03:31,750 --> 00:03:33,375
Meow.

48
00:03:33,458 --> 00:03:36,000
That's right.
Cuteness is justice!

49
00:03:37,166 --> 00:03:38,208
[sighs]

50
00:03:40,416 --> 00:03:43,541
Hey, Asuka, what do you think
of these cat ears?

51
00:03:43,625 --> 00:03:45,875
They're pretty adorable,
aren't they?

52
00:03:45,958 --> 00:03:47,083
[YUMI]
Hold on.

53
00:03:47,166 --> 00:03:50,125
You know those are
bunny ears, right?

54
00:03:50,208 --> 00:03:52,458
Uh, yeah.
of course I do!

55
00:03:52,541 --> 00:03:55,000
But I was thinking of buying
myself a Christmas present.

56
00:03:55,083 --> 00:03:56,750
What do you think, Yumi,

57
00:03:56,833 --> 00:03:58,750
should I wear these bunny ears
whenever I fight from now on?

58
00:03:58,833 --> 00:04:01,250
-Huh?
-[ASUKA shouts]

59
00:04:01,333 --> 00:04:03,291
It's like that thing
you always say.

60
00:04:03,375 --> 00:04:05,125
You know,
"Cuteness is justice!".

61
00:04:05,208 --> 00:04:06,583
[YUMI]
Hmm.

62
00:04:06,666 --> 00:04:08,458
Uh.
Right.

63
00:04:08,541 --> 00:04:11,208
So maybe I'll start fighting
while wearing these ears.

64
00:04:11,291 --> 00:04:12,416
Hwah!

65
00:04:12,500 --> 00:04:13,375
Oh, please.

66
00:04:13,458 --> 00:04:15,625
How silly.

67
00:04:15,708 --> 00:04:17,250
They are super
cute and everything,

68
00:04:17,333 --> 00:04:19,166
but I can only imagine
what Homura would say

69
00:04:19,250 --> 00:04:21,750
if she saw me fighting
with these on my head.

70
00:04:21,833 --> 00:04:23,291
Cut it out, Asuka!

71
00:04:23,375 --> 00:04:25,416
Do you think your ninja missions
are some kind of joke?

72
00:04:25,500 --> 00:04:28,625
You're a shinobi, not a
cosplayer, so get it together!

73
00:04:28,708 --> 00:04:29,833
[sneezes]

74
00:04:31,250 --> 00:04:32,291
[groans]

75
00:04:34,166 --> 00:04:36,375
[YUMI]
I was so surprised at first.

76
00:04:36,458 --> 00:04:38,916
-Special sales all day long!
-Do your shopping here!

77
00:04:39,000 --> 00:04:41,666
[YUMI] I mean, you're
a good ninja like I am.

78
00:04:42,833 --> 00:04:45,500
But somehow, you're friends
with Homura,

79
00:04:45,583 --> 00:04:47,000
and the other evil ninjas.

80
00:04:52,291 --> 00:04:54,416
I get what you're saying,
and we have fought a lot

81
00:04:54,500 --> 00:04:56,916
since we're technically on
different sides and everything.

82
00:04:57,000 --> 00:04:59,958
But Homura and I have a strange
understanding now,

83
00:05:00,041 --> 00:05:01,791
so it just sort of works.

84
00:05:07,625 --> 00:05:08,583
[chuckles]

85
00:05:08,666 --> 00:05:09,791
In fact,

86
00:05:09,875 --> 00:05:11,666
I think she's secretly
a nice person.

87
00:05:11,750 --> 00:05:13,250
[sneezing]

88
00:05:14,208 --> 00:05:15,833
I've been sneezing all day,

89
00:05:15,916 --> 00:05:17,916
and that can only mean that
Asuka's talking about me again!

90
00:05:18,000 --> 00:05:19,416
Hey!

91
00:05:19,500 --> 00:05:22,083
We don't have time
for this stupid part-time job!

92
00:05:22,166 --> 00:05:23,750
If anything, we should
focus on training

93
00:05:23,833 --> 00:05:24,916
so we can take down Asuka

94
00:05:25,000 --> 00:05:27,500
and the others next time
we see them!

95
00:05:27,583 --> 00:05:29,875
Come on, don't you guys think
we should be off training?

96
00:05:29,958 --> 00:05:33,208
No, we love wearing skimpy
Santa suits in snowy weather.

97
00:05:33,291 --> 00:05:35,041
You were the one who said
you wanted

98
00:05:35,125 --> 00:05:36,625
a big turkey
for Christmas.

99
00:05:36,708 --> 00:05:39,000
That stuff costs money.

100
00:05:39,083 --> 00:05:41,458
Being a renegade shinobi
doesn't pay well.

101
00:05:41,541 --> 00:05:44,458
So, we have to work
if we want fresh meat.

102
00:05:44,541 --> 00:05:45,666
That's true, and besides,

103
00:05:45,750 --> 00:05:47,250
I was thinking
it would be kind of nice

104
00:05:47,333 --> 00:05:49,458
to bake a delicious
sprout cake for Christmas.

105
00:05:49,541 --> 00:05:51,125
[scoffs]

106
00:05:51,208 --> 00:05:53,250
It's either training, or turkey.

107
00:05:53,333 --> 00:05:56,125
This is truly
the ultimate decision.

108
00:05:56,208 --> 00:05:57,708
Or is it?

109
00:05:57,791 --> 00:06:00,458
Perhaps there's a way
we can have both!

110
00:06:00,541 --> 00:06:02,250
Watch this!

111
00:06:02,333 --> 00:06:03,875
You see, ladies?

112
00:06:03,958 --> 00:06:05,833
We can train our legs
while still earning money

113
00:06:05,916 --> 00:06:07,250
for our Christmas dinner!

114
00:06:07,333 --> 00:06:08,750
Two birds, one stone!

115
00:06:08,833 --> 00:06:11,791
No, two turkeys with one stone!

116
00:06:11,875 --> 00:06:14,583
Wait, are we gonna have to run
in place like that, too?

117
00:06:14,666 --> 00:06:15,625
Of course!

118
00:06:15,708 --> 00:06:17,625
We're Homura's Crimson Squad.

119
00:06:17,708 --> 00:06:20,250
The family who trains together
stays together!

120
00:06:20,333 --> 00:06:22,458
Are you sure, because
I've never heard of a family

121
00:06:22,541 --> 00:06:23,833
who does that.

122
00:06:23,916 --> 00:06:26,583
She's not going to
drop it, is she?

123
00:06:26,666 --> 00:06:28,250
Probably not.

124
00:06:28,333 --> 00:06:31,791
[HOMURA] Attention shoppers,
Christmas is almost upon us!

125
00:06:31,875 --> 00:06:33,583
So, why not buy
your presents right here?

126
00:06:33,666 --> 00:06:35,583
[ALL]
We have excellent deals!

127
00:06:38,833 --> 00:06:42,500
Well, Yumi?
You done?

128
00:06:42,583 --> 00:06:44,500
Just a minute!

129
00:06:44,583 --> 00:06:46,125
I'm almost ready.

130
00:06:49,208 --> 00:06:51,041
Uh, so does this look okay?

131
00:06:51,125 --> 00:06:53,583
Oh, yeah, it's super adorable!

132
00:06:53,666 --> 00:06:55,375
That dress would be
absolutely perfect for, like,

133
00:06:55,458 --> 00:06:57,000
a Christmas party
or something.

134
00:06:57,083 --> 00:06:58,791
You really think so?

135
00:06:58,875 --> 00:07:00,250
You should totally try

136
00:07:00,333 --> 00:07:02,291
on some of the other
cute outfits they have here.

137
00:07:02,375 --> 00:07:03,666
[gasps]

138
00:07:03,750 --> 00:07:05,708
And I'll do it, too!
[chuckles]

139
00:07:05,791 --> 00:07:06,833
♪

140
00:07:53,166 --> 00:07:54,375
Uh...

141
00:07:54,458 --> 00:07:56,416
I think this one may be
a bit too much.

142
00:07:59,750 --> 00:08:01,000
Yeah.

143
00:08:01,083 --> 00:08:03,458
Or in this case,
it's not enough, am I right?

144
00:08:05,041 --> 00:08:06,708
[BOTH laughing]

145
00:08:10,875 --> 00:08:11,833
[ASUKA giggles]

146
00:08:11,916 --> 00:08:13,000
That was fun!

147
00:08:14,333 --> 00:08:16,750
Honestly, it was all
a little bit embarrassing.

148
00:08:16,833 --> 00:08:17,958
[ASUKA giggles]

149
00:08:18,041 --> 00:08:19,125
[GIRL 1]
You're so cute!

150
00:08:19,208 --> 00:08:20,625
[GIRL 2]
Oh my gosh, you think so?

151
00:08:20,708 --> 00:08:22,833
-Take my picture next okay?
-You're making me blush!

152
00:08:22,916 --> 00:08:24,458
-[GIRL 1] My turn!
-[GIRL 2] Okay!

153
00:08:24,541 --> 00:08:27,291
-[GIRL 1] How's this pose?
-[WAITRESS] Here's your order.

154
00:08:30,458 --> 00:08:31,500
♪

155
00:08:34,708 --> 00:08:36,791
I think I'll snap
a picture, too.

156
00:08:36,875 --> 00:08:38,291
[giggles]

157
00:08:38,375 --> 00:08:40,041
What about you?

158
00:08:40,125 --> 00:08:42,833
This might sound kind of weird,
but I don't have a cellphone.

159
00:08:42,916 --> 00:08:44,083
Seriously?

160
00:08:44,166 --> 00:08:45,750
Yes, my friends
are always bugging me

161
00:08:45,833 --> 00:08:47,791
about how I should get one,

162
00:08:47,875 --> 00:08:50,625
but to be honest I've never seen
the point of them.

163
00:08:50,708 --> 00:08:51,833
-Say cheese!
-Huh?

164
00:08:51,916 --> 00:08:52,791
[camera clicks]

165
00:08:53,875 --> 00:08:55,958
So, how do you
usually contact people

166
00:08:56,041 --> 00:08:57,708
if you don't have
a cell phone?

167
00:08:57,791 --> 00:08:59,208
I just send a letter.

168
00:08:59,291 --> 00:09:01,125
What if you're
in a hurry, though?

169
00:09:01,208 --> 00:09:02,666
A telegram.

170
00:09:02,750 --> 00:09:04,375
Oh, wow.

171
00:09:04,458 --> 00:09:07,583
I didn't know there were people
who still used those things.

172
00:09:07,666 --> 00:09:08,916
Do you think I'd be better off

173
00:09:09,000 --> 00:09:11,166
if I just got a phone
like everyone else?

174
00:09:11,250 --> 00:09:14,166
Hmm. It's difficult to say.

175
00:09:14,250 --> 00:09:16,708
But, if you were to get one,
then we could totally send

176
00:09:16,791 --> 00:09:18,833
each other messages
and stuff, you know?

177
00:09:21,500 --> 00:09:22,791
-[phone chiming]
-Huh?

178
00:09:31,750 --> 00:09:33,500
That sounds like it'd be fun.

179
00:09:40,500 --> 00:09:42,958
I've been thinking a lot lately.

180
00:09:43,041 --> 00:09:45,708
About the real task
we take on as Shinobi.

181
00:09:47,166 --> 00:09:49,166
Pursue justice at all costs.

182
00:09:49,250 --> 00:09:51,375
Even if it means
losing our lives.

183
00:09:51,458 --> 00:09:53,791
We have to do what it takes
to beat the youma.

184
00:09:54,833 --> 00:09:56,541
Well yeah, but I think
all the girls

185
00:09:56,625 --> 00:09:58,750
who became shinobi
are willing to do that.

186
00:09:59,708 --> 00:10:01,166
I know I am.

187
00:10:01,250 --> 00:10:03,916
I guess what I was referring
to were the little gaps

188
00:10:04,000 --> 00:10:06,500
that we have between
our training and missions.

189
00:10:06,583 --> 00:10:09,083
You know, the moments
like this one.

190
00:10:09,166 --> 00:10:11,791
It's important that we don't
take them for granted.

191
00:10:11,875 --> 00:10:13,916
Oh, you're saying work
when it's time to work,

192
00:10:14,000 --> 00:10:15,833
but play when it's time to play.

193
00:10:15,916 --> 00:10:17,666
That's what you mean, right?

194
00:10:18,833 --> 00:10:20,375
[ASUKA giggles]

195
00:10:20,458 --> 00:10:21,708
Yeah.

196
00:10:22,750 --> 00:10:24,500
We are high school girls.

197
00:10:25,500 --> 00:10:27,083
Normally.

198
00:10:27,166 --> 00:10:29,583
If that's all we were, then
we would be free to cut loose

199
00:10:29,666 --> 00:10:31,375
and do whatever we wanted to.

200
00:10:55,916 --> 00:10:58,541
The words "work" and "play"
are kind of funny, you know?

201
00:10:58,625 --> 00:11:01,125
They can be
complete opposites or similar.

202
00:11:01,208 --> 00:11:02,708
It depends, right?

203
00:11:02,791 --> 00:11:05,000
So, in a way, it reminds me
of something else.

204
00:11:05,083 --> 00:11:06,083
Uh?

205
00:11:06,166 --> 00:11:09,041
[YUMI]
"A sword and a shield."

206
00:11:09,125 --> 00:11:10,208
Oh, yeah.

207
00:11:10,291 --> 00:11:12,041
Like my grandpa always says.

208
00:11:12,125 --> 00:11:13,291
Yep.

209
00:11:14,625 --> 00:11:17,666
A sword by itself is only
capable of harming others.

210
00:11:17,750 --> 00:11:21,500
And a shield can protect people,
but it can't do it alone.

211
00:11:21,583 --> 00:11:23,208
That's why it's important
to wield the sword

212
00:11:23,291 --> 00:11:24,541
and the shield together.

213
00:11:24,625 --> 00:11:26,458
To have both is to have power.

214
00:11:26,541 --> 00:11:29,208
[YUMI] If you work too much,
it's exhausting.

215
00:11:29,291 --> 00:11:32,333
And you'll never get stronger
if you just relax all the time.

216
00:11:32,416 --> 00:11:34,416
You're totally right,
they are similar!

217
00:11:37,666 --> 00:11:38,625
Asuka.

218
00:11:38,708 --> 00:11:40,375
I don't see your cat ears.

219
00:11:40,458 --> 00:11:41,333
[gasps]

220
00:11:41,416 --> 00:11:43,708
Oh no!
They're missing!

221
00:11:43,791 --> 00:11:45,208
Maybe they slipped out
of your bag

222
00:11:45,291 --> 00:11:47,791
while we were
walking around earlier.

223
00:11:47,875 --> 00:11:49,583
Aw.
What should I do?

224
00:11:49,666 --> 00:11:51,833
That was the last pair
in the entire store!

225
00:11:51,916 --> 00:11:53,791
Let's go look for them.

226
00:12:10,958 --> 00:12:13,333
[ASUKA] Nobody can see us
back here, right?

227
00:12:13,416 --> 00:12:14,583
Right.

228
00:12:14,666 --> 00:12:16,541
Let's take a little
short cut, then.

229
00:12:23,125 --> 00:12:24,208
Okay, Asuka.

230
00:12:24,291 --> 00:12:25,958
Let's split up
and search the city!

231
00:12:26,041 --> 00:12:27,208
Yeah!

232
00:12:38,791 --> 00:12:39,708
Something wrong?

233
00:12:44,625 --> 00:12:46,125
[HOMURA] Stop in here
for some awesome

234
00:12:46,208 --> 00:12:47,416
Christmas specials!

235
00:12:47,500 --> 00:12:49,250
Come grab a free fly--

236
00:12:52,541 --> 00:12:54,458
-[ASUKA gasps]
-[HOMURA yells]

237
00:12:57,208 --> 00:12:59,375
-No way, Homura?
-Asuka!

238
00:12:59,458 --> 00:13:02,125
You didn't think you could just
ignore me, did you?

239
00:13:02,208 --> 00:13:04,583
I hope you brought your A-game!

240
00:13:04,666 --> 00:13:08,875
[ASUKA grunts]
I don't have time for this!

241
00:13:08,958 --> 00:13:10,333
I'm in huge hurry!

242
00:13:10,416 --> 00:13:12,833
So sorry!
We'll fight later!

243
00:13:15,958 --> 00:13:17,708
Jeez, what's her problem?

244
00:13:20,000 --> 00:13:21,916
[KATSURAGI] We all left
at different times,

245
00:13:22,000 --> 00:13:24,208
but somehow still
ended up together.

246
00:13:24,291 --> 00:13:25,416
Weird, huh?

247
00:13:25,500 --> 00:13:27,041
I don't think
it's that strange,

248
00:13:27,125 --> 00:13:29,666
in fact, I bet that Asuka
is also close by.

249
00:13:29,750 --> 00:13:31,166
Hey, Yagyu.

250
00:13:31,250 --> 00:13:33,750
What did you get me
for Christmas, tell me, tell me!

251
00:13:33,833 --> 00:13:35,708
That would ruin the surprise.

252
00:13:35,791 --> 00:13:37,708
You'll have to wait, Hibari.

253
00:13:37,791 --> 00:13:40,958
Aww. Come on,
Christmas is still so far away.

254
00:13:41,041 --> 00:13:43,750
Please, you have to tell me
now, because if you don't,

255
00:13:43,833 --> 00:13:46,083
then I might die
from curiosity overload!

256
00:13:46,166 --> 00:13:48,333
Wait, can that really happen?

257
00:13:48,416 --> 00:13:50,833
No fair, you're manipulating me
with your cuteness.

258
00:13:50,916 --> 00:13:52,750
No. I have to stay strong,

259
00:13:52,833 --> 00:13:55,833
