Stay on guard.

280
00:14:43,541 --> 00:14:45,250
Right!

281
00:14:50,666 --> 00:14:53,166
He did not!

282
00:14:53,250 --> 00:14:55,000
[MAN]
What about sushi?

283
00:14:56,958 --> 00:14:58,041
[gasps]

284
00:15:02,416 --> 00:15:04,583
And that's why
I quit working there.

285
00:15:04,666 --> 00:15:06,666
Yay, I'm so glad
I found them.

286
00:15:06,750 --> 00:15:08,333
Let's see.

287
00:15:08,416 --> 00:15:10,041
Now I get it.

288
00:15:10,125 --> 00:15:11,333
This is one of those moments

289
00:15:11,416 --> 00:15:13,375
where it'd be good
to have a cell phone.

290
00:15:19,000 --> 00:15:20,750
Wait, are the two
of you shinobi?

291
00:15:24,125 --> 00:15:26,625
A kekkai barrier?

292
00:15:26,708 --> 00:15:28,833
I guess that answers
that question.

293
00:15:28,916 --> 00:15:30,125
Are they evil ninjas?

294
00:15:30,208 --> 00:15:31,750
[IKARUGA]
No, they can't be.

295
00:15:31,833 --> 00:15:33,166
Look at their uniforms.

296
00:15:34,500 --> 00:15:36,541
The Gessen Girls'
Academy Middle School?

297
00:15:37,916 --> 00:15:39,125
No way!

298
00:15:39,208 --> 00:15:40,708
But isn't that where Yumi
goes to school?

299
00:15:40,791 --> 00:15:43,291
So that means they're actually
good ninjas, like we are.

300
00:15:43,375 --> 00:15:44,875
What's up with the
murderous aura then?

301
00:15:44,958 --> 00:15:46,875
Good ninjas like you?

302
00:15:46,958 --> 00:15:48,291
Now there's a joke.

303
00:15:48,375 --> 00:15:49,458
[KATSURAGI]
Excuse me?

304
00:15:49,541 --> 00:15:51,125
Answer me this.

305
00:15:51,208 --> 00:15:53,708
What does it truly mean
to have power?

306
00:15:53,791 --> 00:15:55,666
-What is justice?
-[gasps]

307
00:15:55,750 --> 00:15:58,208
No fair, nobody said
anything about a pop quiz!

308
00:15:59,500 --> 00:16:02,291
She's not here at the moment,
but if I may,

309
00:16:02,375 --> 00:16:04,750
I'd like to quote the words
of a good friend of mine.

310
00:16:04,833 --> 00:16:06,750
Power is a sword and shield.

311
00:16:06,833 --> 00:16:08,916
We take the strength of a sword

312
00:16:09,000 --> 00:16:11,208
and use it as a shield
to protect people.

313
00:16:11,291 --> 00:16:13,291
That's what it means
to have power, and how

314
00:16:13,375 --> 00:16:14,750
I define justice.

315
00:16:14,833 --> 00:16:16,250
Wow, how cliché.

316
00:16:16,333 --> 00:16:18,750
Did you read that in
a greeting card somewhere?

317
00:16:18,833 --> 00:16:21,000
Unfortunately,
what you call justice

318
00:16:21,083 --> 00:16:23,125
is not needed
in the world of shinobi.

319
00:16:23,208 --> 00:16:25,041
It dulls resolve
that should be pure.

320
00:16:25,125 --> 00:16:27,625
[IKARUGA]
What do you want from us?

321
00:16:27,708 --> 00:16:30,166
We simply want
to eliminate you!

322
00:16:30,250 --> 00:16:32,333
With the power of true justice.

323
00:16:36,125 --> 00:16:37,541
[ALL]
Shinobi...

324
00:16:37,625 --> 00:16:40,541
Transformation!

325
00:16:40,625 --> 00:16:42,500
[HIBARI]
Ha!

326
00:16:47,458 --> 00:16:50,125
-[phone ringing]
-[ASUKA gasps]

327
00:16:50,208 --> 00:16:51,833
Uh, hello?

328
00:16:51,916 --> 00:16:53,083
Huh?
Yumi?

329
00:16:53,166 --> 00:16:54,458
Is something wrong?

330
00:16:54,541 --> 00:16:55,791
Where are you calling from?

331
00:16:55,875 --> 00:16:56,875
Whoa.

332
00:16:56,958 --> 00:16:58,583
A payphone, really?

333
00:16:58,666 --> 00:17:01,083
Mm-hm. Mm-hm.
[gasps]

334
00:17:01,166 --> 00:17:03,208
Yay, I can't believe
you actually found them!

335
00:17:03,291 --> 00:17:04,083
[gasps]

336
00:17:04,166 --> 00:17:05,750
Right.

337
00:17:05,833 --> 00:17:08,291
So next I think we should find
a good place to rendezvous.

338
00:17:09,708 --> 00:17:11,375
Yeah, the café should work fine.

339
00:17:11,458 --> 00:17:13,208
I'll see you there!

340
00:17:23,250 --> 00:17:24,166
That's strange.

341
00:17:24,250 --> 00:17:25,958
Something feels off.

342
00:17:37,541 --> 00:17:38,583
[gasps]

343
00:17:40,416 --> 00:17:42,333
No way.
Youma?

344
00:17:45,041 --> 00:17:48,208
Shinobi Transformation!

345
00:17:53,625 --> 00:17:54,833
I am Asuka!

346
00:17:54,916 --> 00:17:56,958
A shinobi who fights
for justice!

347
00:17:59,291 --> 00:18:00,500
[shouts]

348
00:18:00,583 --> 00:18:03,250
-[WOMAN grunts]
-Oh, uh...

349
00:18:03,333 --> 00:18:04,750
Excuse me.

350
00:18:04,833 --> 00:18:05,833
Uh?

351
00:18:11,000 --> 00:18:12,750
A sword and a shield?

352
00:18:12,833 --> 00:18:14,333
How odd.

353
00:18:17,208 --> 00:18:19,416
[ASUKA panting]

354
00:18:23,083 --> 00:18:24,416
[SENKOU]
How pathetic.

355
00:18:24,500 --> 00:18:26,541
Struggling to fight
such weak youma.

356
00:18:31,458 --> 00:18:33,125
Who are you guys?

357
00:18:34,958 --> 00:18:36,500
My name is Gekkou.

358
00:18:38,416 --> 00:18:40,166
And my name's Senkou.

359
00:18:41,541 --> 00:18:43,708
So you're the one,
the foolish girl

360
00:18:43,791 --> 00:18:46,208
who compares power
to a sword and a shield.

361
00:18:46,291 --> 00:18:47,625
[ASUKA gasps]

362
00:18:47,708 --> 00:18:50,000
Your naivete is a virus
that must be contained

363
00:18:50,083 --> 00:18:53,333
before it has a chance to infect
the rest of the good shinobi.

364
00:18:53,416 --> 00:18:56,000
We have no choice
but to eliminate you, Asuka.

365
00:18:56,958 --> 00:18:58,083
Whoa, hold on.

366
00:18:58,166 --> 00:18:59,791
I don't get any of this!

367
00:18:59,875 --> 00:19:00,916
[gasps]

368
00:19:02,125 --> 00:19:03,375
They're fast!

369
00:19:03,458 --> 00:19:05,416
We'll carve this knowledge
into your soul.

370
00:19:06,666 --> 00:19:08,458
This is the purest resolve.

371
00:19:09,875 --> 00:19:11,041
[ASUKA gasps]

372
00:19:19,666 --> 00:19:20,666
[ASUKA shouts]

373
00:19:34,708 --> 00:19:36,625
They're strong!

374
00:19:36,708 --> 00:19:37,791
[SENKOU]
I hope you're not

375
00:19:37,875 --> 00:19:39,291
expecting your friends
to help you,

376
00:19:39,375 --> 00:19:41,875
because they won't.
They're a bit busy.

377
00:19:52,666 --> 00:19:54,000
[ASUKA gasps]

378
00:19:56,541 --> 00:19:57,708
Why?

379
00:19:58,833 --> 00:20:00,375
See, we stopped and had
a little chat

380
00:20:00,458 --> 00:20:01,791
with those girls earlier.

381
00:20:01,875 --> 00:20:03,208
Let's just say
they're well aware

382
00:20:03,291 --> 00:20:05,125
of what our pure
resolve looks like.

383
00:20:06,458 --> 00:20:08,416
What did you do?

384
00:20:08,500 --> 00:20:09,791
Tell me.

385
00:20:09,875 --> 00:20:12,916
What did you do?

386
00:20:13,958 --> 00:20:15,708
Fool.

387
00:20:29,500 --> 00:20:31,166
That was too easy.

388
00:20:34,208 --> 00:20:35,958
-Hold on, Senkou.
-Mm?

389
00:20:39,708 --> 00:20:41,625
No, I won't lose to you.

390
00:20:41,708 --> 00:20:44,041
You're still standing?

391
00:20:45,541 --> 00:20:47,166
Bring it on.

392
00:20:47,250 --> 00:20:52,458
I won't stop until I master
the path of the shinobi!

393
00:21:04,250 --> 00:21:06,333
Asuka!

394
00:21:06,416 --> 00:21:07,708
Asuka.

395
00:21:09,125 --> 00:21:11,333
Asuka.

396
00:21:11,416 --> 00:21:12,750
Asuka!

397
00:21:18,916 --> 00:21:20,750
[YUMI]
Here, I think you dropped this.

398
00:21:23,333 --> 00:21:24,916
Thank you.

399
00:21:25,000 --> 00:21:26,750
It's no problem at all!

400
00:21:30,750 --> 00:21:31,708
I see.

401
00:21:33,666 --> 00:21:35,375
So that girl is Yumi.

402
00:21:41,500 --> 00:21:42,958
♪

403
00:23:33,375 --> 00:23:35,375
